|last = Schwarzbaum|first = Erica|date = August 1, 2017|accessdate = August 4, 2017|publisher = Benzinga}}</ref> On August 3, Coinbase announced that it would start supporting Bitcoin Cash transactions by January 1, 2018, and that users who had any amount of Bitcoin were credited an equal amount of Bitcoin Cash though they could start transacting in it only once Coinbase was ready to transact.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://blog.coinbase.com/update-on-bitcoin-cash-8a67a7e8dbdf|title = Update on Bitcoin Cash|last = Farmer|first = David|date = August 3, 2017|accessdate = August 3, 2017|publisher = Coinbase}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://fortune.com/2017/08/03/coinbase-to-let-users-withdraw-bitcoin-cash-after-outcry/|title = Coinbase to Let Users Withdraw Bitcoin Cash After Outcry|last = Roberts|first = Jeff John|date = August 3, 2017|accessdate = August 4, 2017|publisher = ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]''}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/08/03/coinbase-says-it-will-support-bitcoin-cash-after-all-but-it-isnt-committed-to-trading-yet/?ncid=mobilenavtrend|title = Coinbase says it will support Bitcoin Cash after all — but it isn’t committed to trading yet|last = Russell|first = Jon|date = August 3, 2017|accessdate = August 4, 2017|publisher = ''[[TechCrunch]]''}}</ref>

