BitMEX,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.bitmex.com/site_announcement/policy-on-bitcoin-hard-forks/|title=Policy on Bitcoin Hard Forks|last=Hayes|first=Arthur|date=July 25, 2017|publisher=BitMEX|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref> Exodus, and [[Bitstamp]] announced that they would not support Bitcoin Cash.<ref name=nyt-bitcoin-cash-exchange-support/><ref name="bitcoin-cash-support">{{cite web|url=https://news.bitcoin.com/fork-watch-these-bitcoin-exchanges-will-not-support-bitcoin-cash/|title=Fork Watch: These Bitcoin Exchanges Will Not Support 'Bitcoin Cash'|last=Redman|first=Jaime|date=July 27, 2017|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livebitcoinnews.com/major-exchanges-will-not-support-bitcoin-cash/|title=Most Major Exchanges Will not Support Bitcoin Cash|last=Buntinx|first=JP|date=July 28, 2017|publisher=Live Bitcoin News|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref>

Altcoin exchange Poloniex had not announced a decision as of near the end of July 2017, but said that they were making a decision keeping the security of users' bitcoins in mind.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://poloniex.com/press-releases/2017.07.24-Our-plans-to-handle-potential-BTC-network-disruptions/|title=OUR PLANS TO HANDLE POTENTIAL BTC NETWORK DISRUPTIONS|date=July 24, 2017|publisher=Poloniex|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref><ref name="bitcoin-cash-support" />

